        "scope": "intra-sequence",
        "compliant": true,
        "notes": "STA is required within each sequence: intermediate transitional vectors (ms-seq1-001, ms-seq2-101) are only activated by their predecessors and will deactivate on any non-matching input. A multi-bit jump (e.g. [0,0,0]→[0,1,1], HD=2) would skip the intermediate step and silently abort the sequence. The defined intra-sequence paths all use HD=1. The 'Both Sequences Interleaved' input sequence contains a HD=3 inter-sequence jump ([0,1,1]→[1,0,0]) which is safe because Seq2's initial vector (ms-seq2-100) is always active and requires no predecessor.",
        "maxHammingDistanceInDefinedSequences": 3,
        "maxHammingDistanceIntraSequence": 1,
        "violations": [
          {
            "sequence": "Both Sequences Interleaved",
            "transition": "[0,1,1] → [1,0,0]",
            "hammingDistance": 3,
            "intent": "Inter-sequence jump: Seq1 final → Seq2 initial. Safe because initial vectors are always active.",
            "behavior": "Correct — ms-seq2-100 matches immediately"
          }
